Description:
A Unique Home In A Rewarding Location!
Imagine a location that allows you to have cafes at your doorstep! Literally… Only a ten-minute walk from Coburg Train Station and from Sydney Road's grand shopping strip with plenty of restaurants, cafes & shops! Not only is the location one of the best we have ever seen but so is the modern & chic apartment itself. The unique floorplan includes 2 spacious bedrooms with plenty of wardrobe room. Furthermore, the vast balcony allows the room to entertain all your guests or to spend your summer nights relaxing and sipping on a cold drink…
PROPERTY SPECIFICATIONS:
- Apartment built in 2009 approx.
- Land size 108 m2 approx. Building size of 11 s/q approx.
- BEDROOMS: Bedrooms 1 & 2 include mirrored built in robes, carpet flooring, gas space heater and access to the balcony.
- KITCHEN: Laminate cabinetry, stone benchtops, gas cooktop, range hood, electric oven, single sink, dishwasher, pantry, and tiled flooring.
- MEALS: Open plan meal zone with carpet flooring.
- LIVING: Open plan living zone with carpet flooring.
- BATHROOM/LAUNDRY: Shower, combined toilet, single vanity, 3-in-1 and tiled flooring. Simpson washing machine and single trough.
- HEAT/COOL: 4 gas space heaters and 2 split systems throughout the home.
- OUTDOORS: Spacious balcony with seating space.
- ADDITIONAL: Intercom.
- PARKING: Secure garage space.
- POTENTIAL RENT: $400 - $430 p/w approx.
LOCATION BENEFITS:
- Easy walking distance to Coburg Train Station
- Close to Sydney Road shopping strip
- Located 8.1km's North of the CBD with terrific City Link, Ring Road, major arterial roads and airport access
PREFERRED SALE TERMS:
DEPOSIT:
- 10%
SETTLEMENT:
- 30/60 Days
Buy this unique home today by calling one of our friendly team members Marwan or Donna. It won't last long!
Marwan Abdulwahed: 0420 647 396
Donna Younis: 0407 665 087

Description:
Radiant Terrace In Top Locale
Poised in a tightly held locale, this versatile three/four bedroom Victorian terrace brings together the best of various worlds with city views from the balcony, a sunny northerly rear aspect, bright interior, exceptional convenience and peaceful bird sounds filling the air. Also forming the perfect fourth double bedroom, the lounge is complemented by a dining room/alternative living area and updated kitchen with stainless steel
appliances. Stylish and modern, the bathroom showcases a freestanding bath and frameless rain shower. Split systems provide heating/cooling, there's outstanding storage and classic features include soaring ceilings,
polished floorboards, fireplaces and deep cornices. Convenient off street parking adjoins a rear ROW, while Coburg Market, trains, trams, vibrant Sydney Road and playgrounds are just moments away.

• Formal lounge & dining rooms

Ready to be sold inspection is a must!

Description:
Bright & Spacious Townhouse!
A contemporary townhouse of easy lifestyle living within walking distance to the Upfield Bike Path, vibrant Sydney, Moreland and Melville Road all including cafes, restaurants and public transport.
Once you walk into this charming house you are greeted with a large living area with polished hardwood floors. The large kitchen boasts stainless steel appliances, Chef Gas stove, electric oven, an abundance of storage space, opening up to the dining room with tiled floors flowing through to the north facing and well landscaped courtyard, perfect for entertaining family and friends.
Upstairs offers generous size bedrooms, include BIR's and central bathroom complete with separate shower and bath. Master bedroom has walk in robe and access to central bathroom.
Additionally the home has plenty of natural light throughout, separate laundry with powder room, ducted heating and cooling, reverse cycle split system, intercom and a single car lock up garage with remote.
This property is full of potential, come and see for yourself!

An opulent entertainer's haven
A private haven in the heart of Coburg this four bedroom period home readily balances ornate period detail with modern indoor-outdoor living to deliver a superb family home. Ornate roses and cornices adorn the lofty ceilings of this opulent home featuring four bedrooms with BIR's and two luxury bathrooms before etched glass doors give way to a glorious open plan. Contemporary Style and Architectural Flair
Tucked away in a quiet Coburg cul-de-sac, moments from the buzz of Sydney Road, this trendy townhouse delivers an idyllic executive lifestyle with its clever design, impressive features and rooftop surprise. Bathed in northerly light, the home's classy interior showcases two double bedrooms (one with balcony), stylish central bathroom with floor-to-ceiling tiles and additional powder room (second WC). A perfect choice for professionals and blue-chip investors alike, it's walking distance to trams (Sydney Road and Moreland Road), Moreland Station, local schools, as well as endless shops, cafes and restaurants.

Description:
Prime location with period appeal
This charming double fronted home set amongst wonderful established gardens in a lovely quiet street in one of Coburg's best pockets. Offered in good order with instant period appeal and terrific potential to further improve taking advantage of the large allotment. The light-filled accommodation includes 2 large bedrooms, spacious living & dining rooms, central bathroom, bright kitchen leading to a rear verandah and beautiful established gardens. Conveniently positioned near to Sydney Road transport, shops & cafes, this is a great opportunity to move in immediately and/or renovate/develop (STCA) in this highly sought-after location. Land 479.18 m2 (12.19m x 39.31m approx.) Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
UNDER OFFER
Enjoying easy access to Coburg Village, cosmopolitan Sydney Road, Batman station and Coburg North Primary School, this two bedroom California Bungalow exudes strong market entry, investor and family appeal. High decorative ceilings and substantial rooms define the interior. The family lounge adjoins the open kitchen/dining domain (full complement of appliances) and there's a north facing covered patio overlooking lovely rear landscaped gardens. A large master boasts an elegant bay window, both bedrooms embellished with leadlight. There's also a tidy bathroom, two powder rooms, separate laundry, split system air conditioning, ample driveway parking including carport plus large workshop/shed. In great condition, the home welcomes modernisation whilst a generous allotment of approximately 431m2 may inspire a future extension (subject to council approval).

Description:
Captivating Californian Bungalow.
This darling family home is tastefully refurbished throughout offering rooms of impressive proportion catering to families and entertainers alike. A welcoming traditional façade and stunning established garden set the scene to this wonderful home.
Comprising-
Traditional entry hall
3 well-proportioned bedrooms
Pristine central bathroom & spacious second bathroom
Vast open plan- living/dining/family room
Country style kitchen features timber benchtop and quality appliances
Large laundry with private garden access
Home office & playroom
Accessible side driveway
French doors lead to a picture perfect brick paved and beautifully landscaped rear garden with an array of mature trees and plants, a pathway leading to Calder Reserve Park at the rear of the home makes for perfect Neighbours and the ideal extended entertaining area.
Added Attractions Included: Lofty ceilings, satin finish Baltic pine floor boards, open fire place, traditional leadlight windows, split system heating & cooling & attic storage. All this set on a sunny favorable East/West allotment!
Within a stone's throw to parks, trams, local cafes & restaurants, popular Merri Creek walking trails & local schools makes this a true family home indeed!

Description:
Master Your Destiny
Desirably close to buzzing Sydney Road restaurants, shops and transport, this spacious double fronted, two bedroom home delivers fantastic versatility and a myriad of options. Nestled on approximately 401m2, immediately comfortable whilst offering broad appeal for those looking to enhance, extend, start fresh or develop, (STCA). Comprising a street facing lounge that flows through the central dining room, a sizeable kitchen/meals with gas stove, an abundance of cupboards and counter space, it also features a light filled sunroom. The two double bedrooms come with built-in robes and share a neat bathroom with a shower and vanity, while further features include heating, evaporative cooling, high ceilings, a rear yard, long side driveway and a deep garage. With so many possibilities rolling out before you, this is an excellent opportunity to seize the reins and shape the future to match your desires (subject to relevant approvals).
